Dear Stockholder,

The proxy materials for CardConnect’s July 12, 2016, special meeting are now available for your
review at https://www.cstproxy.com/cardconnect/sm2016.

The proxy materials consist of:

  *   Proxy Form
  *   Notice - CardConnect - Special Meeting

Under Securities and Exchange Commission rules, you are receiving this notice that the proxy
materials for the special meeting of stockholders are available on the Internet. If you would like to
receive a paper or e-mail copy of these documents, you must request one. There is no charge for
requesting a copy. Please make your request for a copy as instructed below on or before July 07,
2016 to facilitate timely delivery.

The purpose of the Special Meeting is to consider and vote on proposals related to the proposed
business combination (the “Business Combination”) between CardConnect, Inc. (“CardConnect”)
and FinTech Acquisition Corp. (“FinTech”), including approval of the merger of FinTech Merger
Sub, Inc., a Delaware corporation, with and into CardConnect, with CardConnect surviving the
merger. CardConnect’s board of directors has determined that each of the proposals to be presented
at the Special Meeting is advisable, fair to and in the best interests of CardConnect and its
stockholders and recommends that CardConnect’s stockholders vote "FOR" each of the
proposals.

The Board of Directors has fixed the close of business on June 20, 2016 as the record date (the
"Record Date") for determining the CardConnect stockholders entitled to receive notice of and to
vote at the special meeting. Only holders of record of shares of CardConnect capital stock on the
Record Date are entitled to notice of, and to vote at, the special meeting.

Your vote is important. Instructions on how to vote, how to attend the special meeting and how to
request a paper or email copy of the proxy materials are all
contained within the proxy materials.

The special meeting will be held at 10:00 A.M., Eastern Time, on July 12, 2016, at the offices of
Ledgewood, P.C., located at Two Commerce Square, 2001 Market Street, Suite 2900,
Philadelphia, PA 19103.

This is not a proxy.
You cannot use this notice to vote these shares.
